title: What makes a Degas a Degas (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
What Makes a Degas a Degas?
Metropolitan Museum of Art & Viking | 1993 | English | 52 pages | PDF | 5 MB


Recognizing and appreciating the work of a particular artist can be as easy as spotting a friend's handwriting. This title covers the life and work of Edgar Degas. The clues to identifying an individual artist's work - colour, line, shape, composition, brushwork and subject matter - are revealed through a detailed exploration of 12 masterpieces. The author also describes Degas's career and the times in which he lived
